This repository orchestrates, but does not vendor, several third-party
projects that carry their own licenses, including:
  - llama.cpp (MIT)               https://github.com/ggml-org/llama.cpp
  - Open WebUI (Open WebUI License, BSD-3-based)
                                  https://github.com/open-webui/open-webui
  - SearXNG (AGPL-3.0)            https://github.com/searxng/searxng
  - MCPO (MIT)                    https://github.com/open-webui/mcpo
  - MCP Python SDK (MIT)          https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/python-sdk
  - OpenCode (MIT)                https://github.com/sst/opencode
  - openai-python (Apache-2.0)    https://github.com/openai/openai-python
  - huggingface_hub (Apache-2.0)  https://github.com/huggingface/huggingface_hub
  - Tailscale (BSD-3-Clause)      https://github.com/tailscale/tailscale
llama.cpp is cloned and built locally (not vendored in this repository's
history); Open WebUI and SearXNG run from their official upstream container
images; the remaining projects are installed from their official
distribution channels. License labels reflect upstream at time of writing —
consult each project for current terms.
Model weights (Qwen, Gemma, etc.) are downloaded separately and are governed
by their own upstream licenses.
